---
layout: layout-base.njk
title: US Cities With the Longest Growing Seasons | GrowByDate
description: Compare U.S. cities by frost-free season length and typical outdoor growing-season window.
canonical: "https://growbydate.com/data/rankings/us-cities-with-the-longest-growing-seasons/"
---

{% set board = usCitiesLongestGrowingSeasons %}
{% set top = board.top %}

<section class="card leaderboardHero">
  <p class="eyebrow">City comparison</p>
  <h1>US Cities With the Longest Growing Seasons</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    This ranking compares U.S. cities by average frost-free growing season length — the window between
    typical last spring frost and first fall frost.
  </p>

  <div class="leaderboardStatGrid" aria-label="Ranking summary">
    {% if top %}
      <div class="leaderboardStat">
        <span class="statLabel">Longest season</span>
        <strong>{{ top.cityName }}</strong>
        <span>{{ top.frostFreeDays }} frost-free days · {{ top.label }}</span>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    <div class="leaderboardStat">
      <span class="statLabel">Cities compared</span>
      <strong>{{ board.entries.length }}</strong>
      <span>U.S. cities with frost-date values</span>
    </div>

    <div class="leaderboardStat">
      <span class="statLabel">Best paired with</span>
      <strong>GDD</strong>
      <span>Long seasons and high heat are related, but not identical.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>The ranking</h2>
  <p>
    Cities are ranked by frost-free days. This is a season-length ranking, not a full crop-success ranking — GDD, water, heat stress, and crop heat needs still matter.
  </p>

  <div class="tableWrap leaderboardTableWrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Rank</th>
          <th>City</th>
          <th>Last spring frost</th>
          <th>First fall frost</th>
          <th>Frost-free days</th>
          <th>Base 50°F GDD</th>
          <th>Season read</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for row in board.entries %}
          <tr>
            <td><strong>#{{ row.rank }}</strong></td>
            <td>
              <a href="{{ row.url }}"><strong>{{ row.cityName }}</strong></a><br>
              <span class="small muted">{{ row.regionName }}, U.S.</span>
            </td>
            <td>{{ row.springFrost }}</td>
            <td>{{ row.fallFrost }}</td>
            <td><strong>{{ row.frostFreeDays }}</strong></td>
            <td>{{ row.gddBase50 if row.gddBase50 != null else "—" }}</td>
            <td>{{ row.label }}</td>
          </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card leaderboardCallout">
  <h2>What this ranking means</h2>
  <p>
    A longer frost-free season usually gives gardeners more room for succession planting and long-maturing crops,
    but it does not always mean the most comfortable or productive growing conditions. Heat stress, drought, humidity, and seasonal GDD still matter.
  </p>
  <p>
    Compare with <a href="/data/rankings/us-cities-with-the-highest-growing-degree-days/">US Cities With the Highest Growing Degree Days</a>
    and the full <a href="/data/frost-dates-by-city/">Frost Dates by City</a> reference.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Methodology</h2>
  <p>{{ board.methodology }}</p>
  <p>{{ board.caveat }}</p>
  <p class="small">
    Download: <a href="/assets/data/rankings/us-cities-with-the-longest-growing-seasons.json">longest U.S. growing seasons JSON</a>.
  </p>
</section>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "ItemList",
  "name": {{ board.title | dump | safe }},
  "description": {{ board.description | dump | safe }},
  "url": "https://growbydate.com/data/rankings/us-cities-with-the-longest-growing-seasons/",
  "numberOfItems": {{ board.entries.length }},
  "itemListElement": [
    {% for row in board.entries %}
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": {{ row.rank }},
        "name": {{ (row.cityName ~ " frost-free growing season") | dump | safe }},
        "url": {{ (site.url ~ row.url) | dump | safe }}
      }{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  ]
}
</script>
